<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14109">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Golf.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11844">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Discuss safety on the golf course. Show that you know first aid for
      injuries or illnesses that could occur while golfing, including lightning,
      heat reactions, sunburn, dehydration, blisters, animal or bug bites,
      poison ivy exposure, sprains, and strains. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/26c7909-iKg?si=ZUt8TQ5_jKrBFdJh" target="_blank"
        >First Aid on the Golf Course (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11845">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Complete ONE of the following options:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11845 mb-requirement-id-11846">
        <strong>Option A—Traditional Golf. </strong>Do ALL of the following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11846 mb-requirement-id-11847">
        (1) Study the USGA <i>Rules of Golf</i> now in use. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://www.usga.org/rules/rules-and-clarifications/rules-and-clarifications.html#!ruletype=fr&amp;section=rule&amp;rulenum=1"
          target="_blank"
          >USGA Rules of Golf (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://rules.usga.org/courses/rules-101/" target="_blank"
          >USGA Rules of Golf (Free Course) (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/jbCekejTJXA?si=bsNNU6FHDV0kRcmb"
          target="_blank"
          >The Golf Clubs in Your Bag (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11847 mb-requirement-id-11848">
        (a) Tell about the three categories of golf etiquette. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Golf/three_categories_of_golf_etiquette.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Three Categories of Golf Etiquette (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11847 mb-requirement-id-11849">
        (b) Demonstrate that you understand the definitions of golf terms.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/3qWh2Wruokg?si=8wh6SORdQITXot0t"
          target="_blank"
          >Basic Golf Terminology (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11847 mb-requirement-id-11850">
        (c) Show that you understand the <i>Rules of Amateur Status.</i>
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/TeMdMFFOaTo?si=v2Fu90PKhD6_ixkf"
          target="_blank"
          >Rules of Amateur Status (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11846 mb-requirement-id-11851">
        (2) Tell about your understanding of the World Handicap System. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/IGZ9IGOAWLw?si=2SS8GJeIHCLr5WRq"
          target="_blank"
          >World Handicap System (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11846 mb-requirement-id-11852">
        (3) Do the following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11852 mb-requirement-id-11853">
        (a) Tell about the early history of golf. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/B8hKb4r0yh4?si=tVKbyMEubsrkD-Xx"
          target="_blank"
          >History of Golf (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11852 mb-requirement-id-11854">
        (b) Describe golf's early years in the United States. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/dlGT57kHEQs?si=fTnLU-rMoGewBsX3"
          target="_blank"
          >The Incomplete History of Golf in America (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11852 mb-requirement-id-11855">
        (c) Tell about the accomplishments of a top golfer of your choice.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.lpga.com/athletes/directory" target="_blank"
          >LPGA Player Profiles (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.pgatour.com/players" target="_blank"
          >PGA Player Profiles (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11846 mb-requirement-id-11856">
        (4) Do the following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11856 mb-requirement-id-11857">
        (a) Tell how golf can contribute to a healthy lifestyle, mentally and
        physically. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/5AIr-qbUpQo?si=ku6iDEKLyB3xyiHf"
          target="_blank"
          >Health Benefits of Golf (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11856 mb-requirement-id-11858">
        (b) Tell how a golf exercise plan can help you play better. Show two
        exercises that would help improve your game. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/02KhVJJEFvM?si=PqS213Jy6w1kVfjm"
          target="_blank"
          >Exercises to Improve Your Game (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11846 mb-requirement-id-11859">
        (5) Show the following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11859 mb-requirement-id-11860">
        (a) The proper grip, stance, posture, and key fundamentals of a good
        swing <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Txjm1TjageQ?si=rXGhp-AOdEgGXYCV"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Swing a Golf Club: 5 Steps for Beginners (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11859 mb-requirement-id-11861">
        (b) Driver played from a tee <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/cia6EeHF7ZQ?si=ISZcQzXQSUXnpgo5"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Hit a Driver from the Tee (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/JVsRCPjYTKQ?si=ErMm05iwjCb7DlMr"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Hit an Iron from the Tee (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11859 mb-requirement-id-11862">
        (c) The fairway wood shot <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Fl-20OtZVoY?si=ReNADzqYp58hFvNT"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Hit a Fairway Wood (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11859 mb-requirement-id-11863">
        (d) The long iron shot <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/hoVIDS6UmFk?si=ubkrvt82P9QLD6lt"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Hit a Long Iron Shot (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11859 mb-requirement-id-11864">
        (e) The short iron shot <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/AAOoy8PPlsY?si=TTb4MX_e1u-zkB56"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Hit a Short Iron Shot (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11859 mb-requirement-id-11865">
        (f) The approach, chip-and-run, and pitch shots <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/dwubg2qgV0A?si=4oC8kpT64DEGCXjv"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Hit a Chip Shot (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11859 mb-requirement-id-11867">
        (g) A recovery shot from a bunker or heavy rough <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/ipY-LZUAYrY?si=Asanfyw1idi8Pe-u"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Hit a Bunker Shot (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/4DT-DAOfAHk?si=TvRiMY0-fHv48rE0"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Hit from the Rough (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11859 mb-requirement-id-11868">
        (h) A sound putting stroke <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/AuyVMXl5iYQ?si=HW_Mtm5l3jq35rE0"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Make Long Putts (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/vexw6VaGZPM?si=fIs9fpc1p2J11teS"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Make Short Putts (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11846 mb-requirement-id-11869">
        (6) Play a minimum of two nine-hole rounds or one 18-hole round of golf
        with another golfer about your age and with your counselor, or an adult
        approved by your counselor. Do the following: <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/RQv8w3kmwjo?si=IRz_DEL9yuh_Ehjo"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Play Your First Round of Golf (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11869 mb-requirement-id-11870">
        (a) Follow the <i>Rules of Golf.</i>
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11869 mb-requirement-id-11871">
        (b) Practice good golf etiquette.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11869 mb-requirement-id-11872">
        (c) Show respect to fellow golfers, committee, sponsor, and gallery.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11846 mb-requirement-id-11873">
        (7) Find out about three careers related to traditional golf. Pick one
        and identify the education, training, and experience required for this
        profession. Discuss this with your counselor, and explain why this
        interests you. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/aeSCbYugQAk?si=7YprTcdLuTWEaugk"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Become a Golf Professional (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/FV0vJxab0QI?si=ezjS41VOHd8kh4nD"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Become a Golf Instructor (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11845 mb-requirement-id-11866">
        <strong>Option B—Disc Golf.</strong> Do ALL of the following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11866 mb-requirement-id-11874">
        (1) Study the <i>PDGA Official Rules of Disc Golf</i> now in use.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.pdga.com/rules/official-rules-disc-golf"
          target="_blank"
          >PDGA Rules of Disc Golf (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/iYxbSRG7xjc" target="_blank"
          >PDGA Rules 1: Overview (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLo_ubqHIquFvqTqm8C8UkLT7dMzc2sd_d"
          target="_blank"
          >PDGA Rules School (playlist)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11874 mb-requirement-id-11875">
        (a) Tell about the six areas of Courtesy (812). <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/8_80I2NenwQ?si=7tHglRmPTWy59pey"
          target="_blank"
          >Disc Course Etiquette (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11874 mb-requirement-id-11876">
        (b) Describe the seven areas of Scoring (808). <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.pdga.com/rules/official-rules-disc-golf/808"
          target="_blank"
          >Disc Golf Scoring Rules (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11866 mb-requirement-id-11877">
        (2) Tell about the history of disc golf and why it is an inclusive game.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.pdga.com/files/disc-golfers-code-en-us_1.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >PDGA Disc Golfer's Code (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11866 mb-requirement-id-11878">
        (3) Do the following: <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/U0sNVO5anuk?si=d_6UcMdJxIxfF98w"
          target="_blank"
          >The History of Disc Golf (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11878 mb-requirement-id-11879">
        (a) Tell about the history of disc golf and why it is an inclusive game.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11878 mb-requirement-id-11880">
        (b) Discuss with your counselor the contributions Ed Headrick made to
        the sport of disc golf.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11878 mb-requirement-id-11881">
        (c) Describe the evolution of disc design.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11878 mb-requirement-id-11882">
        (d) Tell about the accomplishments of a top disc golfer of your choice.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.pdga.com/world-rankings" target="_blank"
          >Top Disc Golfers in the World (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11866 mb-requirement-id-11883">
        (4) Do the following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11883 mb-requirement-id-11884">
        (a) Tell how disc golf can contribute to a healthy lifestyle, mentally
        and physically. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/SkZaOSeLMZw?si=SXifoCdgqPr_99RM"
          target="_blank"
          >Health Benefits of Disc Golf (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11883 mb-requirement-id-11885">
        (b) Tell how a disc golf exercise plan can help you play better. Show
        two exercises that would help improve your game. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Pe3rtET4RUs?si=Ys_Ni1kDwdws-Ra1"
          target="_blank"
          >Disc Golf Exercise Plan (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11866 mb-requirement-id-11886">
        (5) Show the following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11886 mb-requirement-id-11887">
        (a) A good throwing grip <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/hmlPfsFq82s?si=hNn-3ZonabKD7yB9"
          target="_blank"
          >A Throwing Disc (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11886 mb-requirement-id-11888">
        (b) A good runup (X-step) when throwing a disc <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/rvwtWNsgGj0?si=4bdppuGc1eQuxcA0"
          target="_blank"
          >The X-Step Runup (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11886 mb-requirement-id-11889">
        (c) Backhand shot <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/N00BfNwc7ng?si=_5avPATQ6y5cjGAZ"
          target="_blank"
          >The Backhand Shot (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11886 mb-requirement-id-11890">
        (d) Forehand shot <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/mjlBl3vHPLA?si=Mw3qNaYB5JSmB41L"
          target="_blank"
          >Forehand Shot (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11886 mb-requirement-id-11891">
        (e) Overhand shot <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Wf0EX0TlE3U?si=-rDr38GFC_-2Shi1"
          target="_blank"
          >Overhand Shot (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11886 mb-requirement-id-11892">
        (f) Rolling shot <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/SGzd4CddZuY?si=JmwcpKQ9JhhVdda6"
          target="_blank"
          >The Rolling Shot (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11886 mb-requirement-id-11893">
        (g) A good (in-line) putting stance <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/wTx5CzU-PMA?si=BFkyylCTMm9yMfXv"
          target="_blank"
          >The Putting Stance (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11886 mb-requirement-id-11894">
        (h) A good straddle putting stance <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Z0-g3KGpkPU?si=YBT8H5FXfVTKUpjv"
          target="_blank"
          >The Straddle Putt (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11886 mb-requirement-id-11895">
        (i) A good putting grip <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/hdMtc3Go2vU?si=bQ0rKOy3WYwXuTGU"
          target="_blank"
          >Disc Golf Putting Grip (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11886 mb-requirement-id-11896">
        (j) A good putting motion &amp; follow through <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/IKgE6q0YKC8?si=m2GdVwR8irfq4fHz"
          target="_blank"
          >The Putt (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11886 mb-requirement-id-11897">
        (k) The proper use of a mini-marking disc <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/drip90Ta9XQ?si=VXT2OTYHY-tC0iII"
          target="_blank"
          >Using a Mini Marking Disc (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11866 mb-requirement-id-11898">
        (6) Play a minimum of 18-holes of disc golf with another disc golfer
        about your age and with your counselor, or an adult approved by your
        counselor. Do the following: <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/M4bcozlUX9g?si=X_Kwf7_PAcIjPgaq"
          target="_blank"
          >Playing a Round of Disc Golf (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11898 mb-requirement-id-11899">
        (a) Follow the <i>PDGA Official Rules of Disc Golf</i>.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11898 mb-requirement-id-11900">
        (b) Practice good disc golf etiquette.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11898 mb-requirement-id-11901">
        (c) Show respect to fellow disc golfers and other people in the park
        along with any wildlife, trees, and plants on the property.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11866 mb-requirement-id-11902">
        (7) Find out about three careers related to disc golf. Pick one and
        identify the education, training, and experience required for this
        profession. Discuss this with your counselor, and explain why this
        interests you. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/y64MQTh98j4?si=XygGG0xzsfpsQurS"
          target="_blank"
          >Disc Golf as a Career (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/rLiz9krymJk?si=wgL3oVMWKdQ5JxDe"
          target="_blank"
          >Being a Professional Disc Golfer (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
